Hello World Program in Java

Below is the code to display the message "Hello World!" in java.

code:

class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println("Hello World");
    }
}

Output:
Hello World!

Naming Convention:
In both Java and Python, the programmers generally follow pascal case notaion for naming classes.

In Java, System.out.println() statement is used to print a line of output to the console.